# Builder.io Agent Rules

## Component Reuse Policy

### CRITICAL: Always Use Existing Components First

Before creating ANY new UI component, you MUST:

1. **Search for existing components** in these locations (in order):
   - `client/components/ui/` - Living Design 3.5 components
   - `client/components/` - Custom application components
   - Check `guidelines/` folder for component documentation
   - Check existing imports in similar pages

2. **Check the component inventory**:
   ```bash
   # Search for existing components
   ls client/components/ui/
   grep -r "export.*function\|export.*const" client/components/ui/
   ```

3. **Consult design system documentation**:
   - `guidelines/Button.md`
   - `guidelines/` folder for all LD 3.5 component specs
   - Reference implementations in `client/components/ButtonExample.tsx`

### Component Hierarchy (Use in This Order)

1. **Living Design 3.5 Components** (ALWAYS PREFER THESE)
   - Location: `client/components/ui/` with `.module.css` files
   - Examples: `Button.tsx`, `ButtonGroup.tsx`, `Tag.tsx`, `OLQTag.tsx`
   - Import: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button'` (uppercase)

2. **Shadcn/Radix Components** (Use when LD 3.5 not available)
   - Location: `client/components/ui/` with lowercase names
   - Examples: `popover.tsx`, `dialog.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx`
   - Import: `import { Popover } from '@/components/ui/popover'` (lowercase)

3. **Custom Application Components** (Last resort)
   - Only create when no LD 3.5 or Shadcn equivalent exists
   - Must follow LD 3.5 design tokens and patterns
   - Document in guidelines/ folder

### Specific Component Rules

#### Buttons
- **ALWAYS use**: `client/components/ui/Button.tsx` (uppercase B)
- **NEVER create**: Custom button elements with inline styles or hard-coded colors
- **MUST use LD 3.5 tokens**: Button component internally uses all LD semantic tokens
- **Variants**: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `destructive`
- **Sizes**: `small`, `medium`, `large`
- **Import**: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button'`

**Token Usage** (Button component uses these internally - DO NOT override):
- Colors: `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary)`, `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-secondary)`, etc.
- Typography: `var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans)`
- Focus: `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline)`
- Border radius: `9999px` (pill-shaped, per LD 3.5 spec)

Example:

// ✅ CORRECT - Uses Button component with tokens
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
<Button variant="primary" size="medium">Click me</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Custom button with hard-coded colors
<button className="bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Click me</button>

// ❌ WRONG - Hard-coded Walmart blue
<button className="bg-[#0071DC] text-white rounded-full">Click me</button>

// ❌ WRONG - Overriding Button tokens
<Button
  variant="primary"
  className="bg-[#0071DC]"  // Never override tokens!
>
  Click me
</Button>


**Why tokens matter:**
- ✅ Ensures brand consistency across the app
- ✅ Enables theme switching (light/dark mode)
- ✅ Centralizes design updates (change once, updates everywhere)
- ✅ Maintains Living Design 3.5 compliance
- ❌ Hard-coded colors break the design system
- ❌ Inline styles bypass the token system

#### Button Groups
- **ALWAYS use**: `client/components/ui/ButtonGroup.tsx`
- **Never use**: Manual flex containers for buttons
- **Import**: `import { ButtonGroup } from '@/components/ui/ButtonGroup'`

Example:

// ✅ CORRECT
<ButtonGroup>
  <Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>
  <Button variant="primary">Save</Button>
</ButtonGroup>

// ❌ WRONG
<div className="flex gap-4">
  <button>Cancel</button>
  <button>Save</button>
</div>


#### Tags & Badges
- **For OLQ scores**: Use `client/components/ui/olq-tag.tsx` (OLQTag component)
- **For general tags**: Use `client/components/ui/tag.tsx` (Tag component)
- **Never use**: Badge component or custom styled spans for tags

Example:
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';
<OLQTag percentage={85} />

// ✅ CORRECT
import { Tag } from '@/components/ui/tag';
<Tag variant="success">Active</Tag>

// ❌ WRONG
<span className="bg-green-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">Active</span>
```

#### Popovers & Overlays
- **Use**: `client/components/ui/popover.tsx` (Radix Popover)
- **Include arrow**: Import and use `PopoverArrow` component
- **Import**: `import { Popover, PopoverTrigger, PopoverContent, PopoverArrow } from '@/components/ui/popover'`

Example:
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<Popover>
  <PopoverTrigger>Open</PopoverTrigger>
  <PopoverContent>
    <PopoverArrow className="fill-white" />
    Content here
  </PopoverContent>
</Popover>
```

### Before Creating a New Component

Ask yourself:
1. ✅ Did I search `client/components/ui/` for existing components?
2. ✅ Did I check `guidelines/` documentation?
3. ✅ Did I look at similar pages to see what they use?
4. ✅ Can I compose existing components to achieve this?
5. ✅ Is this component truly unique to this feature?

If you answered "no" to any of these, DO NOT create a new component.

### Migration from Old to New

When you find code using old patterns:

**Old Pattern (WRONG)**:
```tsx
<button className="h-10 px-4 bg-[#0071DC] text-white rounded-full">
  Click me
</button>
```

**New Pattern (CORRECT)**:
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
<Button variant="primary" size="small">Click me</Button>
```

### Component Import Paths

**Living Design 3.5 Components (Uppercase)**:
```tsx
import { Button, buttonVariants } from '@/components/ui/Button';  // Primary import
import { ButtonGroup } from '@/components/ui/ButtonGroup';
import { Tag } from '@/components/ui/tag';
import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';
```

**IMPORTANT**: The lowercase `button.tsx` file has been DELETED. Always import from uppercase `Button.tsx`.
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// ❌ WRONG - This file no longer exists!
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
```

**Shadcn/Radix Components (Lowercase)**:
```tsx
import { Popover, PopoverTrigger, PopoverContent } from '@/components/ui/popover';
import { Dialog, DialogTrigger, DialogContent } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
import { Select, SelectTrigger, SelectContent } from '@/components/ui/select';
```

### Living Design 3.5 Token Usage

**CRITICAL**: All components MUST use LD semantic tokens. NEVER use hard-coded colors or values.

#### Button Component Tokens (Built-in)

The Button component (`client/components/ui/Button.tsx`) uses these tokens internally:

**Action Colors (Primary Button)**:
```css
/* These are used inside Button.module.css - DO NOT override */
background: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary);           /* #0071DC - Walmart blue */
background-hover: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-hovered);  /* #0060B8 */
background-pressed: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-pressed); /* #004C94 */
color: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-text-on-fill-primary);        /* #FFFFFF */
```

**Action Colors (Secondary Button)**:
```css
background: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-secondary);         /* #FFFFFF */
border: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-border-secondary);           /* #74767C */
color: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-text-secondary);              /* #2E2F32 */
```

**Action Colors (Destructive Button)**:
```css
background: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-destructive);       /* #ea1100 */
background-hover: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-destructive-hovered);
```

**Focus State**:
```css
outline: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline);             /* #0071DC */
```

#### General Token Usage

When creating NEW components (only if absolutely necessary), use these tokens:

**Colors**:
```css
/* ✅ CORRECT - Always use semantic tokens */
background: var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary);
color: var(--ld-semantic-color-text-primary);
border-color: var(--ld-semantic-color-border-strong);

/* ❌ WRONG - Never hard-code colors */
background: #0071DC;      /* Use var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary) */
color: #2E2F32;           /* Use var(--ld-semantic-color-text-primary) */
border-color: #BABBBE;    /* Use var(--ld-semantic-color-border-strong) */
```

**Typography**:
```css
/* ✅ CORRECT */
font-family: var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans);  /* Everyday Sans UI */
font-weight: 700;                                   /* Bold for buttons */
font-size: 14px;  /* Small */
font-size: 16px;  /* Medium */
font-size: 18px;  /* Large */

/* ❌ WRONG */
font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
font-size: 13px;  /* Non-standard size */
```

**Spacing (for ButtonGroup and layouts)**:
```css
/* ✅ CORRECT */
gap: var(--ld-semantic-spacing-3, 12px);   /* Standard gap */
gap: var(--ld-semantic-spacing-2, 8px);    /* Tight gap */

/* ❌ WRONG */
gap: 10px;  /* Arbitrary value */
```

#### Complete Button Token Reference

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary` | #0071DC | Primary button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-hovered` | #0060B8 | Primary button hover |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-pressed` | #004C94 | Primary button active |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-secondary` | #FFFFFF | Secondary button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-border-secondary` | #74767C | Secondary button border |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-destructive` | #ea1100 | Destructive button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline` | #0071DC | Focus indicator |
| `--ld-semantic-font-family-sans` | Everyday Sans UI | All buttons |
| `--ld-semantic-spacing-3` | 12px | Button group gap |

### Enforcement

When reviewing code or making changes:

1. **Run component audit**:
   ```bash
   # Find potential violations
   grep -r "className=\".*bg-\[#" client/pages/
   grep -r "className=\".*rounded-full.*bg-" client/components/
   ```

2. **Check imports**:
   - Ensure Button imports use uppercase: `from '@/components/ui/Button'`
   - Ensure proper component usage in all new code

3. **Consolidate duplicates**:
   - If you find multiple similar components, consolidate to ONE
   - Update all references to use the canonical component
   - Remove duplicates

### Documentation

When creating a NEW component (only if absolutely necessary):

1. Create the component in `client/components/ui/ComponentName.tsx`
2. Create CSS module: `client/components/ui/ComponentName.module.css`
3. Use LD 3.5 semantic tokens exclusively
4. Create documentation: `guidelines/ComponentName.md`
5. Create example: `client/components/ComponentNameExample.tsx`
6. Update this rules file with the new component

### Summary

**Golden Rules**:
1. 🔍 Search FIRST, create LAST
2. 📚 Use LD 3.5 components when available
3. 🎨 Always use semantic design tokens
4. 🔄 Consolidate duplicates immediately
5. 📖 Document new components thoroughly
6. ✅ Import Button from uppercase path: `'@/components/ui/Button'`
7. 🚫 NEVER create custom buttons with inline styles
8. 🎯 One canonical component per UI pattern

**Violation Examples (NEVER DO THIS)**:
```tsx
// ❌ Custom button
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 rounded">Click</button>

// ❌ Custom tag
<span className="bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-2 rounded">Error</span>

// ❌ Manual button group
<div className="flex gap-4">
  <button>Cancel</button>
  <button>Save</button>
</div>

// ❌ Hard-coded colors
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#0071DC' }}>Content</div>
```

**Correct Examples (ALWAYS DO THIS)**:
```tsx
// ✅ Use Button component
<Button variant="primary">Click</Button>

// ✅ Use Tag component
<Tag variant="error">Error</Tag>

// ✅ Use ButtonGroup
<ButtonGroup>
  <Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>
  <Button variant="primary">Save</Button>
</ButtonGroup>

// ✅ Use design tokens
<div style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--ld-semantic-color-fill-primary)' }}>Content</div>
```

